GET A FIRST LOOK AT  THE PRO PROGRAM
Beyond the evening showcases, Fifty Lab is also a home for international music professionals - labels, agents, curators, media and cultural shapers - all here to meet the artists and industry voices of tomorrow.

For three days, Brussels becomes a space for real conversations, new ideas and future collaborations, with talks, workshops, lunches and informal moments designed to make connections feel natural.

If you’re a music industry professional, explore the programme below and secure your Pro Pass. Come be part of it <33
THE MASTERCLASS
Fifty LabO is partly reserved for our professional visitors but this year, one special Masterclass will remain open to all festival attendees with a regular ticket.

DISCOVER
THE CONFERENCES

Three conferences. Two days. Countless ideas.

While showcases take over the city at night, Fifty LabO is our daytime programme of talks and conferences, bringing together key players from the international music scene to share tools, strategies and perspectives to help you move forward. Discover the themes below

#1 GOING GLOBAL – From local success to global exposureExport strategies, international matchmaking and how to exist on a global level.

#2 IN SYNC – Music for film, fashion, gaming & beyond
Opportunities, creative adaptation and how to unlock new revenue streams through sync.

Share
lunches
If you get your Pro Pass, you’re not just here for music and networking, you’ll also enjoy two shared lunches on Day 2 and Day 3 at Mad Brussels, hosted by La Foodina, the Brussels favorite known for its cult Broodje EPIC and bold, colorful fusion cuisine.
A relaxed moment to connect over great food with inspiring people, the kind of conversations that turn into real collaborations.

AND
DRINKS
After an inspiring day of talks, meetings and networking, our Pro Drink is the perfect way to unwind before diving into the night program.
On Day 1, Day 2 and Day 3, professionals gather in iconic Brussels locations to continue conversations in a relaxed setting, where real connections often start to happen naturally.
No pressure, just good energy, great people and the perfect transition into the evening showcases.
